comment: Crowder (BOS) makes marginal contact with Kidd-Gilchrist (CHA) that does not affect his ability to control the pass.
Smart (BOS) cleanly strips the ball from Kidd-Gilchrist (CHA).
Kidd-Gilchrist (CHA) makes body to body contact with Smart (BOS) that affects his SQBR.
Horford (BOS) sets the screen on Walker (CHA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Zeller (CHA) makes contact to Thomas' (BOS) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Bradley (BOS) makes contact to Batum's (CHA) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Batum (CHA) was attempting a 3pt field goal when fouled is confirmed.
Zeller (CHA) legally contests Thomas' (BOS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
[Observable in enhanced video] Batum (CHA) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Thomas (BOS) makes marginal contact with Walker (CHA) on the perimeter. The foot to foot contact is considered incidental.
Smart (BOS) and Zeller (CHA) briefly engage and separate off the ball.
Thomas (BOS) legally contests Lamb's (CHA) jump shot attempt.
Williams (CHA) makes contact with the ball while part of it still remains in the cylinder above the basket ring.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of offensive basket interference is confirmed.
Roberts (CHA) makes incidental contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Thomas (BOS) makes contact to Roberts' (CHA) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Williams (CHA) commits a take foul on Smart (BOS).
Thomas (BOS) makes incidental contact with Lamb (CHA) that does not affect his FOM.
